The paper focuses on the development of a wireless emotion sensing system that uses computational intelligence to extract physical expression from wireless channel data and recover emotion from the corresponding fingerprints. This involves the use of data mining, theoretical modeling, and efficient computational intelligence mechanisms. The system is designed to be low-cost and applicable in real-world scenarios. Based on these characteristics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Information Theory (cs.IT).
